The implementation of Â InputStream does not return -1Â  for eof.

The java doc of InputStream said "The skip method may, for a variety of reasons, end up skipping over some smaller number of bytes, possibly 0."Â 

For FileInputStream, it allows skipping any number of bytes past the end of the file.

So the method "seek" of InputStreamFSInputWrapper will cause infinite loop ifÂ 
desired exceed end of file
Â 
I reproduced with following case
Â 
{code:java}
